The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Wednesday, May 19, 2004 				 Ficci moots 10-point agenda
 OUR CORRESPONDENT																								New Delhi, May 18: The Federation of Indian Chambers of Commerce and Industry (Ficci) today recommended a 10-point economic agenda for the new government.																								Chamber president Y. K. Modi said that according to the plan there should be an announcement of divestment targets of at least Rs 25,000 crore per annum. The proceeds of which should go to a fund dedicated for socio-economic development of rural India.																								The 10-point agenda states that the government should make specific announcements for public investment in agriculture, rural infrastructure, water, health and education.																								Ficci has further recommended that in the next 100 days the new government should implement targeted subsidies for the poor in the forthcoming budget through direct income transfers. It has also sought to enhance tax revenues to mobilise resources to support increase in public investment. 
